commit(address,uint256).details: See {IBionetExchange} Creates an Exchange between the buyer and seller. Escrows funds. Issues a voucher to the buyer. Emits OfferCommitted. Will revert if:  - Offer doesn't exist  - Offer has been voided  - The buyer doesn't send enough money for the price of the offer

finalize(address,uint256).details: Finalize an exchange. This is an important step in the process. It releases funds, and transfers the IP NFT.  Exchange must be in the 'redeemed' state Possible scenarios: 1. buyer calls to close -> all good, [completed] 2. dispute timer expires -> [completed] Therefore any one can call finalize under the following conditions: - The buyer is the caller, OR - The dispute timer has expired In either case, the exchange will be closed. Emits event on successful close Will revert if caller is not the buyer and the time has not expired

initialize(address,address,address).details: Called after default contructor to set needed addresses

redeem(address,uint256).details: See {IBionetExchange} Called by buyer to redeem a voucher issued during commit. If the voucher expired it's canceled by the protocol and the buyer pays a penalty.  Otherwise we update state, burn the voucher and start the dispute time. Emit event. Will revert if:  - Exchange doesn't exist  - Exchange is NOT in the committed state  - Caller is not the buyer

voidOffer(address,uint256).details: See {IBionetExchange} Sets the offer as voided, which should 'de-list' it on the market. Emits OfferCreated Will revert if:  - Caller is not the seller listed in the offer

cancel(address,uint256).notice: See {IBionetExchange} Only the buyer can cancel.  Doing so is a penalty.  This will release funds and emit an event Will revert if:  - Exchange doesn't exist  - Exchange is NOT in the committed state  - Caller is not the exchange buyer

revoke(address,uint256).notice: See {IBionetExchange} Called by seller to revoke a committment. Also checks redeem timer and may cancel versus revoke if the timer has expired.  If the timer has expired the seller is reimbursed the msg.value sent.  Exchange must be in Committment state. Emits event Will revert if:  - Exchange doesn't exist  - Exchange is NOT in the committed state  - Caller is not the seller

documentation.text:
@dev See {IBionetExchange}
 Called by buyer to redeem a voucher issued during commit.
 If the voucher expired it's canceled by the protocol and
 the buyer pays a penalty.  Otherwise we update state, burn the
 voucher and start the dispute time.
 Emit event.
 Will revert if:
  - Exchange doesn't exist
  - Exchange is NOT in the committed state
  - Caller is not the buyer

documentation.text:
@dev Finalize an exchange.
 This is an important step in the process. It releases funds, and transfers
 the IP NFT.  Exchange must be in the 'redeemed' state
 Possible scenarios:
 1. buyer calls to close -> all good, [completed]
 2. dispute timer expires -> [completed]
 Therefore any one can call finalize under the following conditions:
 - The buyer is the caller, OR
 - The dispute timer has expired
 In either case, the exchange will be closed.
 Emits event on successful close
 Will revert if caller is not the buyer and the time has not expired
